i hate to be a downer, but i didn't love this cake. then again...i'm used to making the traditionally buttery, creamy desserts. the raspberry filling is really necessary in this one. just okay...i'd rather have a small piece of real chocolate cake.

Rating: 4
Using seedless raspberry preserves worked wonderfully, and garnishing the cake with a rim of whole raspberries (as in the picture) made everybody ooh and aah. This was so moist and delicious that nobody believed me when I told them it was both low in fat AND low in calories. A definite winner!

